using git source control

1. branchs
	branch: a pointer to a diff state in the repository.
	it holds a copy of the project.
	current branch: where you write your local project.

2. save a copy of the project 
	commit message: a title to the changes you made.
	commit: saves a copy of the project on your local branch.

3. save a remote
	push: send a copy of the current branch to it's remote
	counter part.

